				\begin{document}$${z}_{i}=\frac{x-\mu }{\sigma }$$\end{document}zi=x−μσwhere zi is the z-score of motif i, x is the motif enrichment within a repertoire, μ = average enrichment of control cohort, and σ is the standard deviation for motif i in the control cohort. A z-score of ≥ 4 was considered positive. Sensitivity and specificity in 28 Chagas and 200 controls were calculated and motifs with a sensitivity <15% or a specificity of <99% were removed.
